                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d930">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6611.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Ciudad
                            Juarez</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso, Texas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reports from the south and west do not show conditions improving. Every
                    indication justifies the claim of the anti-Government faction and they are daily
                    growing in number. It is also becoming apparent that the struggle now augmenting
                    will prove to be a real war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
